{
  "doc_id": "28723",
  "text": "To establish blow-up results in view, we shall use the Lyapunov function V (t) = ∫ S u 3 x (t, x)dx introduced in [CITATION_1] to find some sufficient conditions of blow-up solutions for the µCH equation (Theorem 3.3 and Theorem 3.5) and the µDP equation (Theorem 3.7). Based on the conservation laws H 0 , H 1 and H 2 with the best constant in the Sobolev imbedding H 1 (S) ⊂ L ∞ (S), we are able to improve significantly blow-up results shown in [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] .",
